To find a cut-point in a one-dimensional vector, the authors of GF [madhyastha:20:gf] introduce fast-BIC,
which is a regularized version of the classical two-means criterium [dasgupta:08:random-proj-trees]. Both criteria induce a hard cluster assignment to either the left or right cluster.